In this proclamation, President Donald J. Trump declares September 11, 2020, as Patriot Day in honor of the lives lost during the terrorist attacks on September 11, 2001. He calls upon all departments and agencies of the United States to display the flag at half-staff and invites governors, organizations, and individuals to join in this observance. He also encourages the people of the United States to participate in community service and observe a moment of silence at 8:46 a.m. Eastern Daylight Time to remember the victims of the attacks.